    "# 37. The Equipment Selection Problem (RTG vs. RMG vs. Straddle)\n",
    "## Tier 4: Federated Learning for Equipment Selection\n",
    "\n",
    "### Goal\n",
    "Implement a federated learning system where multiple container terminals collaboratively train equipment selection models without sharing sensitive operational data, creating a global intelligence network that leverages collective experience while preserving data privacy.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Assumptions\n",
    "- Multiple terminals have historical equipment selection data with performance outcomes\n",
    "- Terminals are willing to collaborate but cannot share raw operational data due to privacy concerns\n",
    "- Equipment selection patterns can be learned from historical decisions and outcomes\n",
    "- A global model can capture industry-wide patterns that benefit all participants\n",
    "\n",
    "### Approach (Step-by-Step)\n",
    "1. **Neural Network Architecture**: Design a feedforward network for equipment configuration prediction\n",
    "2. **Feature Engineering**: Extract and normalize terminal characteristics and operational parameters\n",
    "3. **Local Model Training**: Each terminal trains models on its private historical data\n",
    "4. **Federated Averaging**: Aggregate local model updates using weighted averaging based on performance\n",
    "5. **Global Model Evaluation**: Test the federated model across all terminals' test datasets\n",
    "6. **Prediction System**: Use the trained global model for new equipment selection decisions\n",
    "\n",
    "### What to Look for in the Results\n",
    "- Federated learning accuracy improvement over local-only training\n",
    "- Model convergence across federation rounds with performance metrics\n",
    "- Confidence scores and recommendation strength for equipment configurations\n",
    "- Comparison of federated vs. isolated model performance\n",
    "\n",
    "### Concrete Example\n",
    "Federated learning network with 12 major container terminals:\n",
    "- **Terminal A**: 12 RTG cranes, 2.1M TEU annual volume, 65% truck traffic\n",
    "- **Terminal B**: 8 RMG cranes, 1.8M TEU annual volume, 75% truck traffic\n",
    "- **Terminal C**: 18 straddle carriers, 1.5M TEU annual volume, 85% truck traffic\n",
    "- **Target Terminal**: 2.7M TEU projected volume, \$220M budget, mixed traffic profile\n",
    "- **Federation Rounds**: 15 rounds with performance-based client weighting\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why this Tier Exists vs. Previous Tiers\n",
    "**Federated Learning provides:**\n",
    "- **Data Privacy**: Collaborates without sharing sensitive operational data\n",
    "- **Collective Intelligence**: Leverages industry-wide experience from multiple terminals\n",
    "- **Continuous Learning**: Improves over time as more data becomes available\n",
    "- **Adaptability**: Learns diverse operational patterns from different terminal types\n",
    "\n",
    "**Advantages over Mathematical Optimization (Tier 1):**\n",
    "- Uses real historical data rather than theoretical models\n",
    "- Captures complex patterns that are difficult to formulate mathematically\n",
    "- Adapts to changing operational conditions and new equipment types\n",
    "- Provides confidence estimates for recommendations\n",
    "\n",
    "**Advantages over Constraint Propagation (Tier 2):**\n",
    "- Learns from experience rather than explicit rule programming\n",
    "- Handles complex, non-linear relationships automatically\n",
    "- Scales to high-dimensional feature spaces\n",
    "- Provides probabilistic recommendations rather than binary decisions\n",
    "\n",
    "**Advantages over Metaheuristics (Tier 3):**\n",
    "- Data-driven rather than simulation-based\n",
    "- Improves with more data rather than requiring parameter tuning\n",
    "- Provides explainable confidence scores\n",
    "- Can handle categorical and mixed data types naturally\n",
    "\n",
    "**When to use this Tier:**\n",
    "- Multiple terminals with historical equipment selection data\n",
    "- Privacy concerns preventing data sharing\n",
    "- Complex operational patterns difficult to model explicitly\n",
    "- Need for adaptive, continuously improving decision systems"
   ]
